 The St Ivan Rilski Church is the only remaining evidence of the community of Zapalnya , Bulgaria , where residents lived until they were forced to leave their homes to make way for a dam built by the Communist regime .
Named after the patron saint of Bulgaria , the crumbling stone structure now cuts a ghostly figure in a few feet of water at the Zhrebchevo reservoir , near the town of Tvardica .
